spec: multiprocessing_extra49
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html#the-process-class — multiprocessing.Process API"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/process.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/context.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends multiprocessing_extra48.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: Process/Queue/Pool/Lock/Event/Semaphore/Value/Array __name__/__module__, Process.__bases__[0].__name__=='BaseProcess', Process.__qualname__, ProcessError/AuthenticationError/BufferTooShort/TimeoutError identity and bases, cpu_count/get_start_method/set_start_method/get_context/active_children __qualname__, exception __module__ and __len__(), context-bound class __qualname__.__len__() tables, Process method __qualname__.__len__() tables, Pool method tables, Process/Pool __mro__.__len__() tables, __all__ metadata, class __dict__ tables, DefaultContext method qualname lengths, BaseProcess metadata, function __name__.__len__() tables, pool result class tables, Process/__name__=='Process'/__module__=='multiprocessing.context', Queue/__name__=='Queue', Pipe/__name__=='Pipe', Process method __qualname__ string equality for start/run/join/terminate/kill/is_alive/close (extra10 — all == 'BaseProcess.<method>'), function __name__/__module__ equality for cpu_count/current_process/active_children, AuthenticationError/__name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__, ProcessError/__name__/__bases__[0].__name__, BufferTooShort/__name__, TimeoutError/__name__/__bases__[0].__name__, exception __module__ equality, ProcessError/__mro__.__len__()==4, exception subclass MRO depths, class/function qualname string equality tables, context class tables (extra40–extra44), Process/__class__.__name__=='type', cpu_count/__class__.__name__=='method', current_process/__class__.__name__=='function', ProcessError/AuthenticationError/__class__.__name__=='type' (extra45), Process/__class__.__qualname__=='type', ProcessError/__class__.__qualname__=='type', current_process/__class__.__qualname__=='function', cpu_count/__class__.__qualname__=='method', Process/__class__.__module__=='builtins', current_process/__class__.__module__=='builtins', cpu_count/__class__.__module__=='builtins' (extra46), ProcessError/__bases__[0].__name__=='Exception', AuthenticationError/__bases__[0].__name__=='ProcessError', ProcessError/__mro__.__len__()==4, AuthenticationError/__mro__.__len__()==5, ProcessError/__module__=='multiprocessing.context', AuthenticationError/__module__=='multiprocessing.context', Queue/__class__.__name__=='method', Pipe/__class__.__name__=='method' (extra47), Process/__doc__/__class__/__name__=='str', ProcessError/__doc__/__class__/__name__=='str', AuthenticationError/__doc__/__class__/__name__=='str', module __doc__/__class__/__name__=='str', Process/__doc__/__class__/__qualname__=='str', ProcessError/__doc__/__class__/__qualname__=='str', Process/__doc__/__class__/__module__=='builtins', BufferTooShort/__bases__[0].__name__=='ProcessError', BufferTooShort/__mro__.__len__()==5, TimeoutError/__mro__.__len__()==5 (extra48). Process.__init__.__qualname__.__len__()==20 (extra33). Process method __qualname__.__len__() for start(17)/run(15)/join(16)/is_alive(20)/terminate(21)/kill(16) (extra21/extra27/extra28). Process property fget qualname lengths and values (extra23/extra24)."
    - "This spec covers: multiprocessing.Process property descriptor type checks — Process.pid/__class__.__name__=='property'; Process.name/__class__.__name__=='property'; Process.daemon/__class__.__name__=='property'; Process.exitcode/__class__.__name__=='property'; Process.authkey/__class__.__name__=='property'; Process.sentinel/__class__.__name__=='property'; also: Process.__init__.__qualname__ string equality == 'BaseProcess.__init__'."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.pid.__class__.__name__ == 'property'. When a property descriptor is accessed via the class (not an instance), Python's descriptor protocol returns the property object itself rather than invoking the getter. Therefore Process.pid is the property descriptor, and its __class__ is the built-in property type. __class__.__name__ == 'property'. The pid descriptor is defined on BaseProcess (multiprocessing.process.BaseProcess) and inherited by Process via __mro__. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.name.__class__.__name__ == 'property'. Same reasoning as pid: the name descriptor is a property object defined on BaseProcess, inherited by Process, and accessible from the class as the descriptor itself. __class__.__name__ == 'property'. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.daemon.__class__.__name__ == 'property'. The daemon attribute is a read-write property defined on BaseProcess. Accessible from the class as the descriptor object; __class__.__name__ == 'property'. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.exitcode.__class__.__name__ == 'property'. The exitcode attribute is a read-only property defined on BaseProcess that returns the process exit status (or None if not yet exited). Accessible from the class as the descriptor; __class__.__name__ == 'property'. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.authkey.__class__.__name__ == 'property'. The authkey attribute is a read-write property defined on BaseProcess used for authentication of inter-process connections. Accessible from the class as the descriptor; __class__.__name__ == 'property'. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.sentinel.__class__.__name__ == 'property'. The sentinel attribute is a read-only property defined on BaseProcess that returns a file descriptor that becomes ready when the process exits. Accessible from the class as the descriptor; __class__.__name__ == 'property'. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.__init__.__qualname__ == 'BaseProcess.__init__'. Process does not override __init__; it inherits the constructor from BaseProcess. The __qualname__ therefore records the defining class name: 'BaseProcess.__init__'. Length is 20 chars ('BaseProcess.'(12) + '__init__'(8)). The length was captured in extra33; this spec adds the full string equality check. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All property descriptors (pid, name, daemon, exitcode, authkey, sentinel) are defined on multiprocessing.process.BaseProcess and inherited by multiprocessing.Process (which is a context-specific subclass of BaseProcess). Accessing these attributes via the class object returns the property descriptor itself because Python applies the descriptor protocol only on instance access, not class-level access for data descriptors when the receiver is the class. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing.Process property descriptor type checks — extra49
#
# When a property descriptor is accessed via the class (not an instance),
# Python returns the property object itself. This is because data descriptors
# (those with __get__ and __set__ or __delete__) only trigger on instance
# access; class-level access returns the descriptor from the class __dict__
# (or its __mro__ equivalent).
#
# All six public Process attributes that expose process state are properties
# defined on BaseProcess (Lib/multiprocessing/process.py):
#   pid      — process ID (None before start())
#   name     — human-readable process name (read-write)
#   daemon   — daemonic flag (must be set before start())
#   exitcode — exit code (None if not yet terminated)
#   authkey  — bytes authentication key for connections
#   sentinel — file descriptor that becomes ready on exit
#
# For each, Process.<attr>.__class__.__name__ == 'property'.
# No prior multiprocessing spec has observed the __class__.__name__ of these
# descriptors from the class scope.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table multiprocessing_extra49.process_property_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process property descriptor __class__.__name__ in extra49 namespace — pid/name/daemon/exitcode/authkey/sentinel all expose property descriptors when accessed via the class"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: mpmeth49propprop

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [pid,      Process.pid.__class__.__name__.__eq__,      ["property"], true, "Process.pid.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — pid is a read-only property defined on BaseProcess; class-level access returns the descriptor object"]
    - [name,     Process.name.__class__.__name__.__eq__,     ["property"], true, "Process.name.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — name is a read-write property defined on BaseProcess; class-level access returns the descriptor object"]
    - [daemon,   Process.daemon.__class__.__name__.__eq__,   ["property"], true, "Process.daemon.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — daemon is a read-write property defined on BaseProcess; must be set before start()"]
    - [exitcode, Process.exitcode.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["property"], true, "Process.exitcode.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — exitcode is a read-only property defined on BaseProcess; None until process terminates"]
    - [authkey,  Process.authkey.__class__.__name__.__eq__,  ["property"], true, "Process.authkey.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — authkey is a read-write property defined on BaseProcess; bytes key for inter-process authentication"]
    - [sentinel, Process.sentinel.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["property"], true, "Process.sentinel.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — sentinel is a read-only property defined on BaseProcess; fd becomes ready when process exits"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing.Process.__init__ qualname string equality — extra49
#
# Prior spec extra33 captured the length of Process.__init__.__qualname__
# (20 chars: 'BaseProcess.__init__'). This spec adds the full string equality
# check. Process inherits __init__ from BaseProcess without override, so the
# __qualname__ records the original defining class name 'BaseProcess.__init__'.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant multiprocessing_extra49.Process_init_qualname_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.__init__.__qualname__ == 'BaseProcess.__init__' — Process inherits __init__ from BaseProcess without override; qualname records the defining class (20 chars: 'BaseProcess.'(12) + '__init__'(8))"
  category: method_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.__init__.__qualname__.__eq__
  args: ["BaseProcess.__init__"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra49
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant multiprocessing_extra49.Process_pid_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.pid.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — pid is a read-only property defined on BaseProcess; class-level access returns the property descriptor object"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.pid.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["property"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra49.Process_name_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.name.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — name is a read-write property defined on BaseProcess; class-level access returns the property descriptor object"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.name.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["property"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra49.Process_daemon_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.daemon.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — daemon is a read-write property defined on BaseProcess; must be set before start()"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.daemon.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["property"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra49.Process_exitcode_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.exitcode.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — exitcode is a read-only property defined on BaseProcess; None until the process terminates"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.exitcode.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["property"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra49.Process_authkey_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.authkey.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — authkey is a read-write property defined on BaseProcess; bytes key for inter-process authentication"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.authkey.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["property"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra49.Process_sentinel_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.sentinel.__class__.__name__ == 'property' — sentinel is a read-only property defined on BaseProcess; file descriptor ready when process exits"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.sentinel.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["property"]
  expected: true
